# 2026-05-30 12:33:31.013411
+when Reviewing code fast. Key issues found:
+
+Critical bugs:
+
+    background.js uses ES module import { supabase } from './lib/supabase' - MV2 background scripts can't use ES modules. Also lib/supabase.ts is TypeScript, not JS. Background needs to build its own client inline.
+    manifest.json validate CI checks assert 'activeTab' not in m.get('permissions',[]) but openskip/.output/firefox-mv2/manifest.json has activeTab - that's the old WXT output, not the shipping manifest. Root manifest.json is clean.
+    background.js has console.log calls - fails CI.
+    content-scripts/content.js uses console.log - fails CI.
+    manifest.json version is 1.5.3 but manifest-chrome.json is 1.5.1 - stale.
+    bug_report.yml only asks for Firefox version, no Chrome/Edge field - minor but inconsistent with cross-browser claim.
+    background.js supabaseUpsert uses imported client with hardcoded credentials rather than user-configured creds from storage - breaks user's own Supabase.

